(8232, 'metformin hydrochloride er', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Metformin is negligibly bound to plasma proteins and is, therefore, less likely to interact with highly protein-bound drugs such as salicylates, sulfonamides, chloramphenicol, and probenecid, as compared to the sulfonylureas, which are extensively bound to serum proteins.', 'DailyMed'),
